#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:164
msgid ""
"Applying the configuration file to our site is slightly different than if we "
"were using a purchased SSL certificate from another provider (and if we "
"didn't let _certbot_ do it automatically)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:166
msgid ""
"The certificate and chain file are included in a single PEM (Privacy "
"Enhanced Mail) file. This is a common format for all certificate files now, "
"so even though it has \"Mail\" in the reference, it is just a type of "
"certificate file. To illustrate the configuration file, we will show it in "
"it's entirety and then describe what is happening:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:167
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<VirtualHost *:80>\n"
"        ServerName www.yourdomain.com\n"
"        ServerAdmin username@rockylinux.org\n"
"        Redirect / https://www.yourdomain.com/\n"
"</VirtualHost>\n"
"<Virtual Host *:443>\n"
"        ServerName www.yourdomain.com\n"
"        ServerAdmin username@rockylinux.org\n"
"        DocumentRoot /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.www/html\n"
"        DirectoryIndex index.php index.htm index.html\n"
"        Alias /icons/ /var/www/icons/\n"
"        # ScriptAlias /cgi-bin/ /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.www/cgi-bin/\n"
"\n"
"\tCustomLog \"/var/log/httpd/com.yourdomain.www-access_log\" combined\n"
"\tErrorLog  \"/var/log/httpd/com.yourdomain.www-error_log\"\n"
"\n"
"        SSLEngine on\n"
"        SSLProtocol all -SSLv2 -SSLv3 -TLSv1\n"
"        SSLHonorCipherOrder on\n"
"        SSLCipherSuite EECDH+ECDSA+AESGCM:EECDH+aRSA+AESGCM:EECDH+ECDSA+SHA384:EECDH+ECDSA+SHA256:EECDH+aRSA+SHA384\n"
":EECDH+aRSA+SHA256:EECDH+aRSA+RC4:EECDH:EDH+aRSA:RC4:!aNULL:!eNULL:!LOW:!3DES:!MD5:!EXP:!PSK:!SRP:!DSS\n"
"\n"
"        SSLCertificateFile /etc/letsencrypt/live/yourdomain.com/fullchain.pem\n"
"        SSLCertificateKeyFile /etc/letsencrypt/live/yourdomain.com/privkey.pem\n"
"        SSLCertificateChainFile /etc/letsencrypt/live/yourdomain.com/fullchain.pem\n"
"\n"
"        <Directory /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.www/html>\n"
"                Options -ExecCGI -Indexes\n"
"                AllowOverride None\n"
"\n"
"                Order deny,allow\n"
"                Deny from all\n"
"                Allow from all\n"
"\n"
"                Satisfy all\n"
"        </Directory>\n"
"</VirtualHost>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:208
msgid ""
"Here's what's happening above. You may want to review the [Apache Web Server "
"Multi-Site Setup](../web/apache-sites-enabled.md) to see the differences in "
"the application of an SSL purchased from another provider and the Let's "
"Encrypt certificate:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:216
msgid ""
"Even though port 80 (standard http) is listening, we are redirecting all "
"traffic to port 443 (https)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:216
msgid "SSLEngine on - simply says to use SSL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:216
msgid ""
"SSLProtocol all -SSLv2 -SSLv3 -TLSv1 - says to use all available protocols, "
"except those that have been found to have vulnerabilities. You should "
"research periodically which protocols are currently acceptable for use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:216
msgid ""
"SSLHonorCipherOrder on - this deals with the next line regarding the cipher "
"suites, and says to deal with them in the order that they are given. This is "
"another area where you should review the cipher suites that you want to "
"include periodically"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:216
msgid ""
"SSLCertificateFile - this is the PEM file, that contains the site "
"certificate **AND** the intermediate certificate. We still need the "
"'SSLCertificateChainFile' line in our configuration, but it will simply "
"specify the same PEM file again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:216
msgid ""
"SSLCertificateKeyFile - the PEM file for the private key, generated with the "
"_certbot_ request."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:216
msgid ""
"SSLCertificateChainFile - the certificate from your certificate provider, "
"often called the intermediate certificate, in this case exactly like the "
"'SSLCertificateFile' location above."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md:218
msgid ""
"Once you have made all of your changes, simply restart _httpd_ and if it "
"starts test your site to make sure you now have a valid certificate file "
"showing. If so, you are ready to move on to the next step: automation."
msgstr ""

